issues.description: The solution’s addGuestStudents method is declared to return boolean, but the UML diagram in the problem statement specifies a void return type for addGuestStudents(int). This return-type mismatch can confuse students about the expected signature and tests may fail if they implement a void method as instructed.
issues.suggested_fix: Adjust the solution’s addGuestStudents method to return void (removing the boolean return) so it matches the UML and problem specification, or update the UML and instructions if a boolean return value is desired.
